BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:pier-2-artist-in-residence-2027@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260723T160017Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260705
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260706
SUMMARY:Deadline: Pier-2 Art Center Artist-in-Residence Programme (PAIR) 20
 27 (Kaohsiung\, Taiwan)
DESCRIPTION:Pier-2 Artist-in-Residence Programme (PAIR) 2027 welcomes artis
 ts whose practice engages experimental approaches\, cross-disciplinary wor
 k\, and place-based research from Taiwan and abroad. Pier-2 Art Center is 
 a settlement-style arts hub in Kaohsiung\, transformed from former warehou
 se clusters\, known for diversity\, openness\, experimentation and innovat
 ion across visual arts\, music\, theatre\, cultural and creative industrie
 s\, film\, television\, and more. 2027 THEME: 'Beta Port | An Unfinished H
 arbour' - a state of becoming\; Beta Port suggests an unfixed\, in-progres
 s condition embodying openness\, fluidity and ongoing evolution\; An Unfin
 ished Harbour points to a city that continuously retains the potential to 
 be re-examined\, reconnected\, and rearticulated. PAIR approaches the resi
 dency as an open site of artistic production\, supporting artists to devel
 op works and methodologies in dialogue with Kaohsiung through research\, e
 xchange and practice. Artists are invited to take Kaohsiung as a starting 
 point and propose projects emphasising public engagement\, local sensibili
 ty\, and experimental approaches. ELIGIBILITY: open to artists and artisti
 c groups (of two people) of all nationalities with at least two years of e
 xperience in art creation. BENEFITS: studio and living space\; art exchang
 e opportunities\; round-trip economy flight or high-speed rail ticket\; da
 ily allowance of NTD 800 per person/group\; project material subsidy up to
  NTD 35\,000\; an assigned project manager. RESIDENCY 2027 PERIOD: 1 Janua
 ry - 31 December 2027 across four intervals (Jan-Mar\, Apr-Jun\, Jul-Sep\,
  Oct-Dec)\; each selected artist undertakes no less than 60 days and no mo
 re than 90 days. DEADLINE: 5 July 2026.\n\nOrganisation: Pier-2 Art Center
 \nLocation: Kaohsiung\, Taiwan (near the Port of Kaohsiung and the Love Ri
 ver estuary)\nAward: A 33 sqm studio with private bathroom plus 16.5 sqm l
 iving space\; art exchange area and opportunities\; one round-trip economy
  class flight ticket OR one round-trip reserved-seat high-speed rail ticke
 t (depending on artist's place of residence)\; daily living allowance of N
 TD 800 per person or group\; project-based material subsidy up to NTD 35\,
 000\; an assigned project manager. No application fee.\nDuration: 60 to 90
  days within one of four 2027 intervals: January-March\, April-June\, July
 -September\, or October-December\n\nMore: https://www.pier2air.tw/en/?utm_
 source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://www.pier2air.tw/en/?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_m
 edium=referral
LOCATION:Kaohsiung\, Taiwan (near the Port of Kaohsiung and the Love River 
 estuary)
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:transmediale-arko-residency-2027@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260723T160017Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260828
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260829
SUMMARY:Deadline: transmediale x ARKO Residency 2027
DESCRIPTION:Third edition of transmediale's residency in collaboration with
  Arts Council Korea (ARKO)\, awarded to one person of Korean nationality (
 based in Korea or elsewhere) working in digital art and moving image pract
 ices\, design\, sound and media theory. Open to artists\, researchers\, pr
 actitioners\, designers and sound artists across all formats. The two-mont
 h residency comes with an artist fee of EUR 1\,500 per month\, additional 
 production support\, and travel and accommodation support for the festival
  and residency\; duos and collectives are welcome but share the same fee. 
 Part of transmediale's 2027 programme (40th anniversary\, themed 'RFC 40')
 \, which seeks proposals offering alternatives to how we understand\, resp
 ond to and shape our technological conditions\, moving from critique to co
 nstruction outside extractive logics. Deadline: 28 August 2026\, 23:59 CES
 T.\n\nOrganisation: transmediale (in cooperation with Arts Council Korea /
  ARKO)\nLocation: Berlin\, Germany (two-month residency around the transme
 diale festival)\; applicants must be of Korean nationality (based in Korea
  or elsewhere)\nAward: Two-month residency with an artist fee of EUR 1\,50
 0 per month\, additional production support\, plus travel and accommodatio
 n support for the festival and residency. For duos or collectives the fee 
 remains the same and is shared. No application fee.\nDuration: Two-month r
 esidency\n\nMore: https://transmediale.de/en/news/transmediale-x-arko-resi
 dency?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://transmediale.de/en/news/transmediale-x-arko-residency?utm_sourc
 e=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Berlin\, Germany (two-month residency around the transmediale fest
 ival)\; applicants must be of Korean nationality (based in Korea or elsewh
 ere)
END:VEVENT
END:VCALENDAR
